network.param.config

Class FileBulkFileImportConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • network.param.config.FileBulkFileImportConfig
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IBulkFileImportConfig, IAttachment
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ReceiptDocumentFileBulkConfig

    public class FileBulkFileImportConfig
extends java.lang.Object
implements IBulkFileImportConfig
    An abstract representation of local/system file system.

    This class is an official implementation of BulkFileUpload as a onetime or batch wise file upload activity. FileBulkFileUploadConfig defines five categories of operations:

    • Setting up or initialize file config using setConfig this method

    • Based on the config getFileContent will read the file content, if any error while reading this file it will return null, otherwise it will return bytebuffer. addBulkUpload or updateBulkUpload will call while converting XLS into Param internal JSONLD format.

    • Based on the config getSize will return the file size in bytes. This method will be invoked at the time of addBulkUpload or updateBulkUpload for keep track of original size and after reading data from getFileContent(). If both values are different it will throw exception.

    • Based on the config getLastModifiedDate will return file last modified date in bytes. This method will be invoked at the time of addBulkUpload or updateBulkUpload for informational purpose getFileContent().

    • Based on the config getFileExtension will return file extension. addBulkUpload or updateBulkUpload for informational purpose getFileContent().

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Jitendra Kumar Balla, ParamNetwork

        public void setConfig(java.lang.String filePath)
               throws ConfigExistsException,
                      FileNotFoundException
        Sets the file path as a config. Method will set config if previous file config is not set otherwise it will throw an ConfigExistsException exception. 
         x.filePath == null
        then it will set the the config and also path can't be empty or null.

        The method setConfig for class FileBulkFileUploadConfig performs a initialize config operation. First, if config not set and it also checks given path is exists and also it will check can able to read the file then it will set the configuration, Otherwise it will throw an ConfigExistsException|FileNotFoundException.

        Parameters:
        filePath - Local file path
        Throws:
        ConfigExistsException - if the same function is calling multiple times then it will throw FileNotFoundException.
